# GENERAL RULES
- Use React Native only (no web code)
- Do NOT use HTML tags (div, span, section, etc.)
- Do NOT use Tailwind CSS or any web styling system
- Use React Native StyleSheet or compatible libraries only
- Always prefer clean, production-ready code

# PROJECT UNDERSTANDING RULE
- Treat web-react folder as reference only
- Never mix web logic into React Native app
- Do not refactor entire project at once
- Work screen-by-screen

# FILE SCANNING RULE
- Only read files explicitly mentioned by user
- Never scan full repository automatically
- Avoid unnecessary file analysis

# ARCHITECTURE RULE
- Use src folder structure in React Native
- Separate screens by role:
  admin / teacher / student
- Use reusable components folder
- Keep navigation clean and modular

# DEVELOPMENT FLOW RULE
- First setup navigation
- Then auth (login/register)
- Then admin dashboard
- Then teacher dashboard
- Then student dashboard

# CODE QUALITY RULE
- Avoid duplicate components
- Reuse existing logic
- Keep code minimal and readable
- Prefer functional components + hooks

# LIBRARY RULE
- Use React Navigation for routing
- Use Zustand or Context for state
- Use Axios for API calls
- Use AsyncStorage for token storage

# SAFETY RULE
- Never assume missing APIs
- Ask or wait for backend confirmation when needed